interpretation.answer: X-ray: AP and lateral of the left ankle, along with a tibia-fibula view, demonstrate a dislocated ankle with syndesmotic diastasis and an associated oblique midshaft oblique fibula fracture.

management.answer: ORIF of Syndesmosis + Deltoid Ligament; ORIF of syndemosis only w/ 2 standard 4.0 screws alone, crossing 4 cortices (If opting to fix deltoid ligament -> open w/ suture anchors).
